    "For example, Brophy et al.'s (2023) BoostIn adapts TracIn for gradient-boosted decision tree ensembles.",
    "Unlike TracIn which uses a novel definition of influence (51), Chen et al.'s (2021) hypergradient data relevance analysis (HyDRa) estimates the leave-one-out influence (8).",
    "HyDRa leverages the same Taylor series-based analysis as Koh & Liang's (2017) influence functions.",
    "The key difference is that HyDRa addresses a fundamental mismatch between influence functions' assumptions and deep models.",
